It's wonderful how green onions just grow out of bulbs if you place them in water and even after you harvest them they regenerate at least once more. You'd assume green onions are something you'd have to jet in from the third world in winter but you can just grow them at home
Like they taste like springtime but you can just put a bunch of regular onions in jars of water in ur kitchen and they will spring green leaves in a few days. The freshness just blossoms in them.

It has a line like "you can find something better than death anywhere". You just have to struggle. The rooster is the only animal still in its youth and he is the last one they pick up on the way. The old animals' willingness to survive ends up saving him too. Brutal, happy tale.

The Town Musicians of Bremen is a hardcore fairy tale. A bunch of old animals about to be killed over no longer being able to work forced to struggle for survival and make a new beginning. Like if that dog they shoot in Of Mice and Men bit the man's hand and ran off in the night.
